🔹 🎯 Task: Stats Reporter
You are writing a lightweight statistics utility that accepts a variable number of integer scores.
📥 Input:
int... scores;
⚙️ Requirements:
•
Write a method report(int... scores) that calculates and prints the count, sum, min, max, and average of the provided scores
•
Average must be printed with 2 decimal places
•
If no arguments are passed, print "No scores provided"
⚠️ Watch out:
•
In JS you'd use rest params (...scores) and scores is a plain array — same syntax, same feel. In Java, int... scores is also just an int[] inside the method, but the trap is trying to call array methods like .length() (it's a field: .length, no parentheses) or assuming it's an Integer[] and calling .equals() — it's a primitive array.
•
Integer division strikes again: sum / scores.length drops the decimal. Cast one operand to double before dividing.
📤 Output format:
Count: X
Sum:   X
Min:   X
Max:   X
Avg:   X.XX
or
No scores provided
📌 Test cases:
Input: report(4, 7, 2, 9, 1)
Output:
Count: 5
Sum:   23
Min:   1
Max:   9
Avg:   4.60

Input: report(42)
Output:
Count: 1
Sum:   42
Min:   42
Max:   42
Avg:   42.00

Input: report(-5, -5, -5)
Output:
Count: 3
Sum:   -15
Min:   -5
Max:   -5
Avg:   -5.00

Input: report()
Output:
No scores provided